      <description>&lt;p&gt;My friend &lt;a href=&#34;https://testingwithmarie.com&#34;&gt;Marie Cruz&lt;/a&gt; and I presented today at &lt;a href=&#34;https://agiletestingdays.com/&#34;&gt;Agile Testing Days 2023&lt;/a&gt; in Potsdam, Germany. Our talk was called &lt;a href=&#34;https://agiletestingdays.com/2023/session/adobo-and-avocados-intersectionality-in-tech-and-devrel/&#34;&gt;Adobo &amp;amp; Avocados: Intersectionality in Tech and DevRel&lt;/a&gt;. We talked about what intersectionality is, shared our personal experiences regarding diversity and intersecting identities, and gave tips on how to think about intersectionality as we build and use software. You can find the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.canva.com/design/DAFzmIZBsAM/vuZZ7KE4fHxczHYdwZTvmw/view?utm_content=DAFzmIZBsAM&amp;amp;utm_campaign=designshare&amp;amp;utm_medium=link&amp;amp;utm_source=editor&#34;&gt;slides here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
